ening\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 379}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ad campaign for Adidas' new retro sneakers, called the SL72s, was a nod to the 1972 Munich Olympics.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 402, \"end\": 408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.450108651758856e-21, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ad campaign\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"the SL72s\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"a nod\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 457}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1972 Munich Olympics\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 485}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Released earlier in July, the advertisement featured Hadid holding a bouquet of flowers while wearing the shoes, which originally debuted in 1972 for the Munich Games.\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 654, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 511}, {\"ngram\": \"the advertisement\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"Hadid\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"a bouquet\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 563}, {\"ngram\": \"flowers\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"the shoes\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"the Munich Games\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that year's games are widely known for the dark tragedy that took place in Munich's Olympic Village: An attack committed by a Palestinian group called Black September, who killed two Israeli athletes on Sept. 5, 1972.\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 735, \"end\": 741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"score\": 0.9990013261122169, \"rank\": 0.0009809073296866606, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich\"}, {\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9998582340502328, \"rank\": 0.0001417659743790755, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9968677879683298, \"rank\": 0.0020706646971653375, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that year's games\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 677}, {\"ngram\": \"the dark tragedy\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 715}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 731}, {\"ngram\": \"Black September\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"Sept.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nine others who were taken hostage later died during a failed rescue attempt.\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nine others\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"hostage\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 912}, {\"ngram\": \"a failed rescue attempt\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 954}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Backlash in response to the Adidas campaign was immediate, as were attacks directed against Hadid, who is half-Palestinian and has advocated for Palestinian rights and donated money to relief efforts in the Gaza Strip.\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.450108651758856e-21, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}, {\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"scor